</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MonstersInc" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MonstersInc">Monsters, Inc.</a></em>, Mike tries bribing a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfHeartedHenchman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfHeartedHenchman">Half-Hearted Henchman</a> when threatened by a torture device, making this overlap with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathByMaterialism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathByMaterialism">Death by Materialism</a> (although it's possible no bribe would have saved him):
<div class="indent"><strong>Mike:</strong> You like cars? Because I got a really nice car. You let me go, I'll give you... a ride... in the car.
</div></li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/LeroyAndStitch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/LeroyAndStitch">Leroy &amp; Stitch</a></em>, Lilo tries to get 625 to let her use his interstellar communicator by offering him a sandwich. 625 makes, gives away, and eats sandwiches <em>all the time</em>... but he accepts the bribe, because no one has ever made sandwiches <em>for him</em>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BecauseYouWereNiceToMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BecauseYouWereNiceToMe">so he's actually touched by the offer</a>.
