</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TotalDramaPresentsTheRidonculousRace" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TotalDramaPresentsTheRidonculousRace">Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race</a></em>, Dwayne Sr. tries to bribe the new host Don out of receiving a penalty by offering him coupons. The first coupon was for 25&cent; off Eggie Muffins, the second was expired.
</li></ul></li><li> Highroller of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Hero108" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Hero108">Hero: 108</a></em> managed to turn all the animal species against the humans, with a simple offering of candy.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Recess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Recess">Recess</a></em> had this a few times, since the main characters were children and were bribing their fellow students. Aside from one occurrence where Gus didn't bring a permission slip to a carnival and TJ tried to bribe the teacher into letting him come anyway with a quarter.
